From TAMMY R HEALY Subject Re SDA Doctrinal Distinctives In article M joseph dale fisher writes There is a book provided by the SDA which is entitled The Seventh Day Adventist Church believes or something like It is a basic coverage of the ideas that SDA's hold For further info about it please write me later once I get the actual title and or copyright date or Celia Chan because she first introduced me to the book I must also add that she is NOT a member of the SDA anymore The book is called basic fundamental beliefs or something very close to the number IS not I have a copy at home i'm away at Tammy